# Shell scripts must be LF everywhere.
#
# core.autocrlf=true rewrites the working tree to CRLF on checkout. Cloud
# sandboxes sync those disk bytes verbatim, and Linux sh/bash choke on \r —
# `set -euo pipefail\r` reads as an invalid option, the shell exits 2, and
# exit 2 is the hook protocol's DENY code, fail-closing every tool call
# (2026-07-17 hook outage). Pinning eol=lf makes checkout produce LF on
# Windows too, so synced bytes are always Linux-safe.
*.sh              text eol=lf
hooks/hooks.json  text eol=lf
